                  <interp inst="t17810425-49-crimeloc242" type="placeName" value="Minories"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17810425-49-crimeloc242" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17810425-49-off239 t17810425-49-crimeloc242"></join>, on the 28th of February, about four in the afternoon, a gentleman stopped me, and told me my pocket had been picked. I had used my handkerchief not two minutes before; I found it missing. I pursued the prisoner; I was informed he had picked my pocket; I overtook him in the Minories; I stopped him, and took my handkerchief out of his pocket.</p>
               <p>- WARREN sworn.</p>
               <p>I am a constable; I saw the handkerchief taken out of his pocket.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I did not steal the handkerchief; I picked it up in the street, and put it into my pocket.</p>
